Sentencas: A long-term stability study of an anode-supported NiO/YSZ-YSZ-LSM/YSZ microtubular cell was performed, under low fuel utilization conditions, using pure humidified hydrogen as fuel at the anode side and air at the cathode side.
Titulo: Long-Term Stability Studies of Anode-Supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: A first galvanometric test was performed at 766 degrees C and 200mAcm(-2), measuring a power output at 0.5V of approximate to 250mWcm(-2).
Titulo: Long-Term Stability Studies of Anode-Supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: During the test, some electrical contact breakdowns at the anode current collector caused sudden current shutdowns and start-up events.
Titulo: Long-Term Stability Studies of Anode-Supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In spite of this, the cell performance remains unchanged.
Titulo: Long-Term Stability Studies of Anode-Supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: After a period of 325h, the cell temperature and the current density was raised to 873 degrees C and 500mAcm(-2), and the cell power output at 0.5V was approximate to 600mWcm(-2).
Titulo: Long-Term Stability Studies of Anode-Supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Several partial reoxidation events due to disturbance in fuel supply occurred, but no apparent degradation was observed.
Titulo: Long-Term Stability Studies of Anode-Supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: On the contrary, a small increase in the cell output power of about 4%/1,000h after 654h under current load was obtained.
Titulo: Long-Term Stability Studies of Anode-Supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The excellent cell aging behavior is discussed in connection to cell configuration.
Titulo: Long-Term Stability Studies of Anode-Supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Finally, the experiment concluded when the cell suffered irreversible damage due to an accidental interruption of fuel supply, causing a full reoxidation of the anode support and cracking of the thin YSZ electrolyte.
Titulo: Long-Term Stability Studies of Anode-Supported Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
